{"id":"kapow-0b1","title":"Log config admin API endpoint","description":"Add an admin HTTP endpoint (e.g. PUT /private/log-config) that allows changing log settings at runtime without restart: global log level, per-category log levels, log destinations (stderr, file path, both). Should be restricted to the private route group (no public access). Depends on the LevelVar, swappable writer, and routing handler features being in place.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-02-22T17:21:06Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","updated_at":"2026-03-02T13:56:03Z","closed_at":"2026-03-02T13:56:03Z","close_reason":"Merged to main from swarm/kapow-0b1"}
{"id":"kapow-0bm","title":"Web unit test infrastructure: Vitest + Testing Library","description":"Install and configure Vitest (with @testing-library/react, @testing-library/user-event, jsdom). Add coverage config targeting 80% threshold. Write smoke tests for Button, Card, and the Home landing page. Add a web-test target to the root Makefile.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-02-19T00:59:26Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","updated_at":"2026-02-19T02:03:37Z","closed_at":"2026-02-19T02:03:37Z","close_reason":"Vitest + Testing Library + happy-dom installed and configured. 12 smoke tests across Button (4), Card (2), and Home (6). 80% coverage thresholds configured. web-test and web-test-coverage targets added to root and web Makefiles."}
{"id":"kapow-0fw","title":"Dev DB container with fixture data","description":"Current state: make dev runs a postgres container with sample fixture data (100 institutions via samplesql). This task creates a standalone compose service loaded with the full dataset (complete.sql.xz, ~3000 institutions), independent of the API/web dev processes.

Add a docker-compose.yml (or compose/db.yml) defining a single postgres+postgis service that loads real institution data on first start.

On startup the container should:
1. Decompress common/src/main/resources/data/complete.sql.xz
2. Execute the resulting SQL (full pg_dump — handles schema, extensions, data, and REFRESH MATERIALIZED VIEW)

The service must expose postgres on a stable local port (e.g. 5433 to avoid colliding with a dev postgres on 5432) and accept connections with published credentials.

Add a Makefile target (e.g. make dev-db-up / make dev-db-down) so developers can start and stop the database independently of the API and web processes. Document the DATABASE_URL to use when running the API locally against this container.

This task covers the database layer only. The full wired environment (API + web) is a separate task (kapow-9fm).","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"task","owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-02-20T01:58:23Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","updated_at":"2026-02-24T21:53:00Z"}
