{"id":"kapow-17of","title":"Implement match-review subcommand","description":"match-review subcommand. Loads unmatched name report from last import run. Displays each unmatched name with top fuzzy candidates. --approve ID persists match as new alias in search_base.institution_alias. --reject ID marks as known non-match. Tracks review state in local JSON file. Done when: can review unmatched names and persist aliases.","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-03-02T23:23:31Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","updated_at":"2026-03-02T23:23:31Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"kapow-17of","depends_on_id":"kapow-3ui2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-02T17:26:53Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","metadata":"{}"},{"issue_id":"kapow-17of","depends_on_id":"kapow-o0j","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-02T17:41:07Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","metadata":"{}"}]}
{"id":"kapow-1am","title":"Add GraphQL institution detail query","description":"Add an institution(unitID: String!) GraphQL query that returns the full denormalized record for a single institution from dataset_merged. The search query returns a subset of fields (name, city, state, coords); this query returns the complete data including NCES stats, rankings, weather, etc. This is needed as a prerequisite for the WebMCP browser integration (kapow-33m) and will also be used by the frontend institution detail page.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-02-22T20:55:49Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","updated_at":"2026-02-23T17:32:15Z","closed_at":"2026-02-23T17:32:15Z","close_reason":"Implemented institution detail GraphQL query with JSONObject scalar, resolver, pgxmock tests, and integration test. Merged to main and pushed."}
{"id":"kapow-1b5","title":"Hot-reloadable log level via slog.LevelVar","description":"Replace the static slog.Level in config.LogHandler() with an *slog.LevelVar stored on Config (or a package-level var). Pass it into HandlerOptions{Level: &levelVar} so the global log level can be changed at runtime without a restart. This is a prerequisite for the admin endpoint that triggers reloads.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-02-22T17:21:01Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","updated_at":"2026-02-22T20:56:05Z","closed_at":"2026-02-22T20:56:05Z","close_reason":"Replaced static slog.Level with slog.LevelVar in Config. LogHandler() now sets a LevelVar, exposed via LogLevelVar(), enabling runtime log level changes. Added ParseLogLevel() helper. 100% test coverage on config package."}
