{"id":"kapow-1wo","title":"Move generated schema.sql out of gitignored path","description":"schema.sql is generated by make schema-gen (scripts/gen-schema.sh) into common/src/main/resources/schema/schema.sql, which is explicitly gitignored. Move it to a different directory (e.g. generated/ or docs/schema/) so it can be tracked in git, and remove the .gitignore entry. The file is useful as a quick reference for the full DB schema without running migrations.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-02-21T20:02:42Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","updated_at":"2026-02-24T04:19:28Z","closed_at":"2026-02-24T04:19:28Z","close_reason":"Won't do: schema.sql is fully derivable from migrations, committing it adds sync risk and noisy diffs with no consumer in the build/deploy pipeline. Only 5 migration files make direct reading easy. Current gitignored + on-demand generation is the right approach."}
